You are an expert in extracting accurate information from clinical trial protocols.

## Task ##
Identify and extract all **Prohibited Medications** listed in the protocol, including medication categories and specific prohibited drugs or drug classes.

## Field Definition ##
**Prohibited Medications** are drugs, biologics, or therapeutic agents that participants must not use during the study.  
They are usually described in sections like “Prohibited Medications,” “Restrictions on Concomitant Medications,” or “Prohibited Therapies.”

## How to Identify ##
- Look for headings or sections titled:
  - “Prohibited Medications”
  - “Prohibited or Restricted Therapies”
  - “Restrictions on Concomitant Therapy”
- Identify drug categories or examples, often formatted as:
  - Category headers (e.g., “Biologics:”, “Other:”)
  - Lists or bullet points (e.g., “• Anti-TNF agents”, “• Live vaccines”)
- Sometimes includes timing or rationale (e.g., “within 8 weeks prior to screening”, “to avoid immune interference”).

## Extraction Rules ##
For each prohibited medication category:
- **category** – The name or grouping under which medications are listed (e.g., “Biologics”, “Other”, “Immunosuppressants”).
- **items** – List of prohibited drugs, classes, or types mentioned under that category.
- **details** – Any timing, condition, or restriction notes (e.g., “within 12 weeks before screening”, “during study treatment”).

## Output Format (JSON) ##
{
  "prohibited_medications": [
    {
      "category": "<Category name>",
      "items": ["<Drug or class>", "<Drug or class>"],
      "details": "<Restriction or timing rule, if any>"
    },
    {
      "category": "<Category name>",
      "items": ["<Drug or class>", "<Drug or class>"],
      "details": "<Restriction or timing rule, if any>"
    }
    ...
  ]
}

## Additional Notes ##
- If no category is listed, group all items under `"category": "Other"`.
- Do not include allowed or background medications.
- Strictly use exact verbatim and exact text present in the content, don't rephrase anything.